<P style="margin:0px" align=center>F-7</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-size:12pt; page-break-before:always" align=center><B>ENDURANCE EXPLORATION GROUP LLC</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><B>(A Development Stage Company)</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><B>NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><B>SEPTEMBER 30, 2013</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:5.533px; margin-bottom:5.533px" align=justify><B>NOTE A - SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Organization</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>Endurance Exploration Group LLC (the &#147;Company,&#148; &#147;Endurance,&#148; &#147;us,&#148; &#147;we&#148; or &#147;our&#148;) was formed in the State of Florida on June 8, 2009 as a Florida Limited Liability Company. &nbsp;Endurance is engaged in the archaeologically sensitive exploration and recovery of deep-ocean shipwrecks throughout the world. The Company intends to recover bullion precious metals, numismatic-grade coinage, high-value non-ferrous metals and other valuable cargos from both historic and modern shipwrecks. &nbsp;Our corporate headquarters are located in Clearwater, Florida.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Basis of Presentation</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>These consolidated financial statements include the assets and liabilities of Endurance Explorer Group, LLC and a wholly owned Panamanian subsidiary formed to hold the registry of a research vessel. Revenues and expenses in the subsidiary are included as of the date of its formation or acquisition. All material intercompany transactions have been eliminated.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>The Company is a development stage company and during the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 and the period from inception (June 8, 2009) through September 30, 2013, significant losses have been incurred. &nbsp;The Company has experienced negative cash flows from operations since the inception of the Company. &nbsp;These circumstances result in substantial doubt as to the ability of the Company to continue as a going concern. &nbsp;The Company will need to obtain additional funding in the future in order to finance its business strategy, operations and growth through the issuance of equity, debt or collaboration. &nbsp;The failure to obtain this additional funding would be detrimental to the Company. &nbsp;The accompanying financial statements do not include any adjustments relating to the recoverability and classification of asset carrying amounts or the amount and classification of liabilities that might result from the outcome of this uncertainty.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Summary of Significant Accounting Policies</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>This summary of significant accounting policies of the Company is presented to assist in understanding our financial statements. The financial statements and notes are representations of the Company&#146;s management who are responsible for their integrity and objectivity and have prepared them in accordance with our customary accounting practices.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Use of Estimates</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>Management uses estimates and assumptions in preparing these financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. Those estimates and assumptions affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities, the disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities, and the reported revenues and expenses. Actual results could vary from the estimates that were used.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Revenue Recognition</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>The Company currently has no revenues.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Cash and Cash Equivalents</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>Cash and cash equivalents include cash on hand and cash in banks. We also consider all highly liquid investments with a maturity of three months or less when purchased to be cash equivalents.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Inventory</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>We record our inventory at the lower of cost or market. &nbsp;As of September 30, 2013 and 2012 and December 31, 2012 and 2011, the Company has no inventory.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR>
<BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center>F-8</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; page-break-before:always" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Long-Lived Assets</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>Our policy is to recognize impairment losses relating to long-lived assets in accordance with the Accounting Standards Codification (&#147;ASC&#148;) topic for Property, Plant and Equipment. Decisions are based on several factors, including, but not limited to, management&#146;s plans for future operations, recent operating results and projected cash flows.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>Property and Equipment and Depreciation</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>Property and equipment is stated at historical cost. Depreciation is provided using the straight-line method at rates based on the assets&#146; estimated useful lives which are normally between three and ten years. &nbsp;Major overhaul items (such as engines or generators) that enhance or extend the useful life of vessel related assets qualify to be capitalized and depreciated over the useful life or remaining life of that asset, whichever is shorter. Certain major repair items required by industry standards to ensure a vessel&#146;s seaworthiness also qualify to be capitalized and depreciated over the period of time until the next scheduled planned major maintenance for that item. All other repairs and maintenance are accounted for under the direct-expensing method and are expensed when incurred.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B><U>Advertising </U></B>The Company expenses the costs of advertising, including promotional expenses, as incurred. &nbsp;Advertising expenses for the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and for the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 were approximately $6,140 and $0, and $1,913 and $0 respectively.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B><U>Income Taxes</U></B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><FONT style="background-color:#FFFFFF">The Company is a limited liability company treated as a partnership for federal and state income tax purposes with all income tax liabilities and/or benefits of the Company being passed through to the members. As such, no recognition of federal or state income taxes for the Company has been provided for in the accompanying financial statements. Any uncertain tax position taken by the members is not an uncertain position of the Company.</FONT></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><FONT style="background-color:#FFFFFF">For purposes of these statements the Company has accounted for income taxes using the liability method of recognizing income tax assets and liabilities. &nbsp;The asset and liability approach requires the recognition of deferred tax assets and liabilities for the expected future tax consequences of temporary differences between the carrying amounts and the tax bases of assets and liabilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;A valuation allowance is provided to offset any net deferred tax assets for which management believes it is more likely than not that the net deferred asset will not be realized</FONT></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<A NAME="page_39"></A><P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B><U>Fair Value of Financial Instruments</U></B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>The fair value of financial instruments, which include cash, loans receivable, accounts payable and accrued expenses and advances from related parties were estimated to approximate their carrying values due to the immediate or short-term maturity of these financial instruments. Management is of the opinion that the Company is not exposed to significant interest, currency or credit risks arising from financial instruments.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<A NAME="page_40"></A><P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B><U>New Accounting Pronouncements</U></B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>The Company reviews new accounting standards as issued. No new standards had any material effect on these financial statements. The accounting pronouncements issued subsequent to the date of these financial statements that were considered significant by management were evaluated for the potential effect on these consolidated financial statements. Management does not believe any of the subsequent pronouncements will have a material effect on these consolidated financial statements as presented and does not anticipate the need for any future restatement of these consolidated financial statements because of the retro-active application of any accounting pronouncements issued subsequent to September 30, 2013 through the date these financial statements were issued.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>NOTE B &#150; GOING CONCERN MATTERS</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>The accompanying financial statements have been prepared on a going concern basis, which contemplates the realization of assets and the satisfaction of liabilities in the normal course of business. As shown in the accompanying financial statements for the period June 9, 2008 (date of inception) to September 30, 2013, the Company incurred losses of $1,598,477. The Company currently has no revenue. &nbsp;These factors, among others, indicate that the Company may not be able to continue as a going concern for a reasonable period of time.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify>The Company's existence is dependent upon management's ability to develop profitable operations and resolve its liquidity problems. The accompanying financial statements do not include any adjustments that might result should the Company be unable to continue as a going concern.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR>
<BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center>F-9</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; page-break-before:always" align=justify><BR></P>
<A NAME="page_41"></A><P style="margin:0px" align=justify><B>NOTE C &#150; ADVANCES FROM RELATED PARTIES AND RELATED PARTY TRANSACTIONS</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><FONT style="background-color:#FFFFFF">Prior to the period ended September 30, 2013, the Company's significant shareholders had advanced funds to the Company for working capital purposes. During the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011, shareholders advanced funds to the Company as capital contributions. &nbsp;</FONT></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><FONT style="background-color:#FFFFFF">On June 19, 2012, the Company borrowed $60,000 from Micah Eldred, one of its members, under a demand promissory note bearing interest at 5%. &nbsp;The note has no stipulated maturity date. &nbsp;The Company has made no payments on this note, but is accruing interest on a monthly basis at the stipulated interest rate. </FONT></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><FONT style="background-color:#FFFFFF">Total amounts due to related parties through advances and the promissory note were $60,000, $60,000 and $60,000 and $0 as of September 30, 2013 and 2012 and December 31, 2012 and 2011 respectively. &nbsp;Except for the terms stipulated in the promissory note, all other amounts advanced are unsecured, non-interest bearing and have no specific terms of repayment.</FONT></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<A NAME="page_42"></A><P style="margin:0px"><B>NOTE D &#150; COMMITMENTS</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><FONT style="background-color:#FFFFFF">Commencing July 1, 2012, the Company rents a warehouse space utilized as a workshop and for storage of equipment. &nbsp;The space is rented on a month to month basis for $1.070 per month. &nbsp;Rent expense was $8,573 and $3,861 and $6,420 and $0.00 for the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and for the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 respectively.</FONT></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>

</TD></TR>

<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px">The tax effects of the temporary differences between reportable financial statement income and taxable income are recognized as deferred tax assets and liabilities.</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px">In assessing the realizability of deferred tax assets, management considers whether it is more likely than not that some portion or all of the deferred tax assets will not be realized.&nbsp;&nbsp;The ultimate realization of deferred tax assets is dependent upon the generation of future taxable income during the periods in which those temporary differences become deductible.&nbsp;&nbsp;Management considers the scheduled reversal of deferred tax liabilities, projected future taxable income and tax planning strategies in making this assessment.</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px">The historical earnings history of the Company does not utilizing the net operating losses in the near future therefore the net deferred tax assets have been fully offset by a 100% valuation allowance.&nbsp;&nbsp;There were no net deferred tax assets at September 30, 2013 of 2012 or December 31, 2012 or 2011.</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px">The net operating losses of approximately $792,700 will begin to expire in 2029. &nbsp;At September 30, 2013, the tax returns for 2009, 2010 and 2011 were open for inspection by federal and state agencies. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>

<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px">Management has evaluated subsequent events through December 13, 2013, which represents the date the financial statements were issued, and have no reportable events.</P>

<P style="margin:0px; padding-left:-36px; text-indent:36px"><B>Notes:</B> Pro Forma Adjustments</P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:-2px; text-indent:60px; width:84px; float:left">(a)</P>
<P style="margin:0px; padding-left:84px; text-indent:-2px" align=justify>Reflects the effect of the business combination by the acquisition of Endurance Exploration Group LLC through the issuance of 20,550,539 shares of the Company&#146;s common stock in exchange for all of the membership interests, and a simultaneous issuance of 12,733,499 shares of the Company&#146;s common stock as a conversion of $291,890 of related party debt on the books of Tecton. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:-2px; text-indent:60px; width:84px; clear:left; float:left">(b)</P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:11.133px; padding-left:84px; text-indent:-2px" align=justify>Reflects the elimination of intercompany loan receivable and payable balance of $2,705 between the two companies.</P>

	<us-gaap:SignificantAccountingPoliciesTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE A - SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Organization&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Endurance Exploration Group LLC (the &amp;#147;Company,&amp;#148; &amp;#147;Endurance,&amp;#148; &amp;#147;us,&amp;#148; &amp;#147;we&amp;#148; or &amp;#147;our&amp;#148;) was formed in the State of Florida on June 8, 2009 as a Florida Limited Liability Company.&amp;#160; Endurance is engaged in the archaeologically sensitive exploration and recovery of deep-ocean shipwrecks throughout the world. The Company intends to recover bullion precious metals, numismatic-grade coinage, high-value non-ferrous metals and other valuable cargos from both historic and modern shipwrecks.&amp;#160; Our corporate headquarters are located in Clearwater, Florida.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Basis of Presentation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;These consolidated financial statements include the assets and liabilities of Endurance Explorer Group, LLC and a wholly owned Panamanian subsidiary formed to hold the registry of a research vessel. Revenues and expenses in the subsidiary are included as of the date of its formation or acquisition. All material intercompany transactions have been eliminated.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;The Company is a development stage company and during the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 and the period from inception (June 8, 2009) through September 30, 2013, significant losses have been incurred.&amp;#160; The Company has experienced negative cash flows from operations since the inception of the Company.&amp;#160; These circumstances result in substantial doubt as to the ability of the Company to continue as a going concern.&amp;#160; The Company will need to obtain additional funding in the future in order to finance its business strategy, operations and growth through the issuance of equity, debt or collaboration.&amp;#160; The failure to obtain this additional funding would be detrimental to the Company.&amp;#160; The accompanying financial statements do not include any adjustments relating to the recoverability and classification of asset carrying amounts or the amount and classification of liabilities that might result from the outcome of this uncertainty.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Summary of Significant Accounting Policies&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;This summary of significant accounting policies of the Company is presented to assist in understanding our financial statements. The financial statements and notes are representations of the Company&amp;#146;s management who are responsible for their integrity and objectivity and have prepared them in accordance with our customary accounting practices.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Use of Estimates&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Management uses estimates and assumptions in preparing these financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. Those estimates and assumptions affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities, the disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities, and the reported revenues and expenses. Actual results could vary from the estimates that were used.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Revenue Recognition&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;The Company currently has no revenues.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cash and Cash Equivalents&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Cash and cash equivalents include cash on hand and cash in banks. We also consider all highly liquid investments with a maturity of three months or less when purchased to be cash equivalents.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Inventory&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;We record our inventory at the lower of cost or market.&amp;#160; As of September 30, 2013 and 2012 and December 31, 2012 and 2011, the Company has no inventory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Long-Lived Assets&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Our policy is to recognize impairment losses relating to long-lived assets in accordance with the Accounting Standards Codification (&amp;#147;ASC&amp;#148;) topic for Property, Plant and Equipment. Decisions are based on several factors, including, but not limited to, management&amp;#146;s plans for future operations, recent operating results and projected cash flows.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Property and Equipment and Depreciation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Property and equipment is stated at historical cost. Depreciation is provided using the straight-line method at rates based on the assets&amp;#146; estimated useful lives which are normally between three and ten years.&amp;#160; Major overhaul items (such as engines or generators) that enhance or extend the useful life of vessel related assets qualify to be capitalized and depreciated over the useful life or remaining life of that asset, whichever is shorter. Certain major repair items required by industry standards to ensure a vessel&amp;#146;s seaworthiness also qualify to be capitalized and depreciated over the period of time until the next scheduled planned major maintenance for that item. All other repairs and maintenance are accounted for under the direct-expensing method and are expensed when incurred.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Advertising &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The Company expenses the costs of advertising, including promotional expenses, as incurred.&amp;#160; Advertising expenses for the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and for the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 were approximately $6,140 and $0, and $1,913 and $0 respectively.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Income Taxes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;The Company is a limited liability company treated as a partnership for federal and state income tax purposes with all income tax liabilities and/or benefits of the Company being passed through to the members. As such, no recognition of federal or state income taxes for the Company has been provided for in the accompanying financial statements. Any uncertain tax position taken by the members is not an uncertain position of the Company.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;For purposes of these statements the Company has accounted for income taxes using the liability method of recognizing income tax assets and liabilities.&amp;#160; The asset and liability approach requires the recognition of deferred tax assets and liabilities for the expected future tax consequences of temporary differences between the carrying amounts and the tax bases of assets and liabilities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;A valuation allowance is provided to offset any net deferred tax assets for which management believes it is more likely than not that the net deferred asset will not be realized.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fair Value of Financial Instruments&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The fair value of financial instruments, which include cash, loans receivable, accounts payable and accrued expenses and advances from related parties were estimated to approximate their carrying values due to the immediate or short-term maturity of these financial instruments. Management is of the opinion that the Company is not exposed to significant interest, currency or credit risks arising from financial instruments.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;New Accounting Pronouncements&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The Company reviews new accounting standards as issued. No new standards had any material effect on these financial statements. The accounting pronouncements issued subsequent to the date of these financial statements that were considered significant by management were evaluated for the potential effect on these consolidated financial statements. Management does not believe any of the subsequent pronouncements will have a material effect on these consolidated financial statements as presented and does not anticipate the need for any future restatement of these consolidated financial statements because of the retro-active application of any accounting pronouncements issued subsequent to September 30, 2013 through the date these financial statements were issued.&lt;/p&gt; </us-gaap:SignificantAccountingPoliciesTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:LiquidityDisclosureGoingConcernNote contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE B &amp;#150; GOING CONCERN MATTERS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The accompanying financial statements have been prepared on a going concern basis, which contemplates the realization of assets and the satisfaction of liabilities in the normal course of business. As shown in the accompanying financial statements for the period June 9, 2008 (date of inception) to September 30, 2013, the Company incurred losses of $1,598,477. The Company currently has no revenue.&amp;#160; These factors, among others, indicate that the Company may not be able to continue as a going concern for a reasonable period of time.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The Company&apos;s existence is dependent upon management&apos;s ability to develop profitable operations and resolve its liquidity problems. The accompanying financial statements do not include any adjustments that might result should the Company be unable to continue as a going concern.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:LiquidityDisclosureGoingConcernNote>
	<us-gaap:RelatedPartyTransactionsDisclosureTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE C &amp;#150; ADVANCES FROM RELATED PARTIES AND RELATED PARTY TRANSACTIONS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;Prior to the period ended September 30, 2013, the Company&apos;s significant shareholders had advanced funds to the Company for working capital purposes. During the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011, shareholders advanced funds to the Company as capital contributions.&amp;#160; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;On June 19, 2012, the Company borrowed $60,000 from Micah Eldred, one of its members, under a demand promissory note bearing interest at 5%.&amp;#160; The note has no stipulated maturity date.&amp;#160; The Company has made no payments on this note, but is accruing interest on a monthly basis at the stipulated interest rate. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;Total amounts due to related parties through advances and the promissory note were $60,000, $60,000 and $60,000 and $0 as of September 30, 2013 and 2012 and December 31, 2012 and 2011 respectively.&amp;#160; Except for the terms stipulated in the promissory note, all other amounts advanced are unsecured, non-interest bearing and have no specific terms of repayment.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:RelatedPartyTransactionsDisclosureTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:CommitmentsDisclosureTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE D &amp;#150; COMMITMENTS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;Commencing July 1, 2012, the Company rents a warehouse space utilized as a workshop and for storage of equipment.&amp;#160; The space is rented on a month to month basis for $1,070 per month.&amp;#160; Rent expense was $8,573 and $3,861 and $6,420 and $0 for the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and for the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 respectively.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:CommitmentsDisclosureTextBlock>

&lt;p align=&quot;right&quot; style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:right;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;-&amp;#160;&amp;#160; &lt;p align=&quot;right&quot; style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:right;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; &lt;td width=&quot;15&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; style=&apos;width:11.2pt;border:none;border-bottom:double windowtext 2.25pt;background:#B6DDE8;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;height:13.5pt&apos;&gt; &lt;p align=&quot;right&quot; style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:right;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; &lt;td width=&quot;67&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; style=&apos;width:50.0pt;border:none;border-bottom:double windowtext 2.25pt;background:#B6DDE8;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;height:13.5pt&apos;&gt; &lt;p align=&quot;right&quot; style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:right;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; &lt;/tr&gt; &lt;/table&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The tax effects of the temporary differences between reportable financial statement income and taxable income are recognized as deferred tax assets and liabilities.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;In assessing the realizability of deferred tax assets, management considers whether it is more likely than not that some portion or all of the deferred tax assets will not be realized.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The ultimate realization of deferred tax assets is dependent upon the generation of future taxable income during the periods in which those temporary differences become deductible.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Management considers the scheduled reversal of deferred tax liabilities, projected future taxable income and tax planning strategies in making this assessment.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The historical earnings history of the Company does not utilizing the net operating losses in the near future therefore the net deferred tax assets have been fully offset by a 100% valuation allowance.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;There were no net deferred tax assets at September 30, 2013 of 2012 or December 31, 2012 or 2011.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The net operating losses of approximately $792,700 will begin to expire in 2029.&amp;#160; At September 30, 2013, the tax returns for 2009, 2010 and 2011 were open for inspection by federal and state agencies.&amp;#160; &lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:IncomeTaxDisclosureTextBlock>

	<us-gaap:OrganizationConsolidationAndPresentationOfFinancialStatementsDisclosureTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Organization&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Endurance Exploration Group LLC (the &amp;#147;Company,&amp;#148; &amp;#147;Endurance,&amp;#148; &amp;#147;us,&amp;#148; &amp;#147;we&amp;#148; or &amp;#147;our&amp;#148;) was formed in the State of Florida on June 8, 2009 as a Florida Limited Liability Company.&amp;#160; Endurance is engaged in the archaeologically sensitive exploration and recovery of deep-ocean shipwrecks throughout the world. The Company intends to recover bullion precious metals, numismatic-grade coinage, high-value non-ferrous metals and other valuable cargos from both historic and modern shipwrecks.&amp;#160; Our corporate headquarters are located in Clearwater, Florida.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:OrganizationConsolidationAndPresentationOfFinancialStatementsDisclosureTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:BasisOfAccountingPolicyPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Basis of Presentation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;These consolidated financial statements include the assets and liabilities of Endurance Explorer Group, LLC and a wholly owned Panamanian subsidiary formed to hold the registry of a research vessel. Revenues and expenses in the subsidiary are included as of the date of its formation or acquisition. All material intercompany transactions have been eliminated.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;The Company is a development stage company and during the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 and the period from inception (June 8, 2009) through September 30, 2013, significant losses have been incurred.&amp;#160; The Company has experienced negative cash flows from operations since the inception of the Company.&amp;#160; These circumstances result in substantial doubt as to the ability of the Company to continue as a going concern.&amp;#160; The Company will need to obtain additional funding in the future in order to finance its business strategy, operations and growth through the issuance of equity, debt or collaboration.&amp;#160; The failure to obtain this additional funding would be detrimental to the Company.&amp;#160; The accompanying financial statements do not include any adjustments relating to the recoverability and classification of asset carrying amounts or the amount and classification of liabilities that might result from the outcome of this uncertainty.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:BasisOfAccountingPolicyPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:OrganizationConsolidationAndPresentationOfFinancialStatementsDisclosureAndSignificantAccountingPoliciesTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Summary of Significant Accounting Policies&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;This summary of significant accounting policies of the Company is presented to assist in understanding our financial statements. 	<us-gaap:UseOfEstimates contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Use of Estimates&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Management uses estimates and assumptions in preparing these financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. Those estimates and assumptions affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities, the disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities, and the reported revenues and expenses. Actual results could vary from the estimates that were used.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:UseOfEstimates>
	<us-gaap:RevenueRecognitionPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Revenue Recognition&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;The Company currently has no revenues.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:RevenueRecognitionPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:CashAndCashEquivalentsPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cash and Cash Equivalents&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Cash and cash equivalents include cash on hand and cash in banks. We also consider all highly liquid investments with a maturity of three months or less when purchased to be cash equivalents.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:CashAndCashEquivalentsPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:InventoryPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Inventory&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;We record our inventory at the lower of cost or market.&amp;#160; As of September 30, 2013 and 2012 and December 31, 2012 and 2011, the Company has no inventory.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:InventoryPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:ImpairmentOrDisposalOfLongLivedAssetsPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Long-Lived Assets&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Our policy is to recognize impairment losses relating to long-lived assets in accordance with the Accounting Standards Codification (&amp;#147;ASC&amp;#148;) topic for Property, Plant and Equipment. Decisions are based on several factors, including, but not limited to, management&amp;#146;s plans for future operations, recent operating results and projected cash flows.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:ImpairmentOrDisposalOfLongLivedAssetsPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:PropertyPlantAndEquipmentPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Property and Equipment and Depreciation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;text-autospace:none&apos;&gt;Property and equipment is stated at historical cost. Depreciation is provided using the straight-line method at rates based on the assets&amp;#146; estimated useful lives which are normally between three and ten years.&amp;#160; Major overhaul items (such as engines or generators) that enhance or extend the useful life of vessel related assets qualify to be capitalized and depreciated over the useful life or remaining life of that asset, whichever is shorter. Certain major repair items required by industry standards to ensure a vessel&amp;#146;s seaworthiness also qualify to be capitalized and depreciated over the period of time until the next scheduled planned major maintenance for that item. All other repairs and maintenance are accounted for under the direct-expensing method and are expensed when incurred.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:PropertyPlantAndEquipmentPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:AdvertisingCostsPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Advertising &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The Company expenses the costs of advertising, including promotional expenses, as incurred.&amp;#160; Advertising expenses for the nine months ended September 30, 2013 and 2012 and for the years ended December 31, 2012 and 2011 were approximately $6,140 and $0, and $1,913 and $0 respectively.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:AdvertisingCostsPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:IncomeTaxPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Income Taxes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;The Company is a limited liability company treated as a partnership for federal and state income tax purposes with all income tax liabilities and/or benefits of the Company being passed through to the members. As such, no recognition of federal or state income taxes for the Company has been provided for in the accompanying financial statements. Any uncertain tax position taken by the members is not an uncertain position of the Company.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal;background:white&apos;&gt;For purposes of these statements the Company has accounted for income taxes using the liability method of recognizing income tax assets and liabilities.&amp;#160; The asset and liability approach requires the recognition of deferred tax assets and liabilities for the expected future tax consequences of temporary differences between the carrying amounts and the tax bases of assets and liabilities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;A valuation allowance is provided to offset any net deferred tax assets for which management believes it is more likely than not that the net deferred asset will not be realized.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:IncomeTaxPolicyTextBlock>
	<us-gaap:FairValueOfFinancialInstrumentsPolicy contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fair Value of Financial Instruments&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The fair value of financial instruments, which include cash, loans receivable, accounts payable and accrued expenses and advances from related parties were estimated to approximate their carrying values due to the immediate or short-term maturity of these financial instruments. Management is of the opinion that the Company is not exposed to significant interest, currency or credit risks arising from financial instruments.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:FairValueOfFinancialInstrumentsPolicy>
	<us-gaap:NewAccountingPronouncementsPolicyPolicyTextBlock contextRef='D130101_130930'>&lt;!--egx--&gt;&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&lt;b&gt;New Accounting Pronouncements&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:115%;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;line-height:normal&apos;&gt;The Company reviews new accounting standards as issued. No new standards had any material effect on these financial statements. The accounting pronouncements issued subsequent to the date of these financial statements that were considered significant by management were evaluated for the potential effect on these consolidated financial statements. Management does not believe any of the subsequent pronouncements will have a material effect on these consolidated financial statements as presented and does not anticipate the need for any future restatement of these consolidated financial statements because of the retro-active application of any accounting pronouncements issued subsequent to September 30, 2013 through the date these financial statements were issued.&lt;/p&gt;</us-gaap:NewAccountingPronouncementsPolicyPolicyTextBlock>

<BODY style="margin-top:0;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">
<DIV style="width:624px"><P style="margin:0px; font-size:11pt" align=right><B>EXHIBIT 21</B></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px" align=right><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px" align=right><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px" align=right><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px; font-size:11pt" align=center><B>SUBSIDIARIES OF TECTON CORPORATION</B></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px" align=right><img src="exhibit21002.gif" alt="[exhibit21002.gif]" align=middle height=336.8 width=575.933></P>

<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:11pt" align=center>1</P>

<DOCUMENT>
<TYPE>EX-3.5
<SEQUENCE>10
<FILENAME>exhibit35.htm
<DESCRIPTION>EXHIBIT 3.5
<TEXT>
<!doctype html public "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Converted by EDGARwiz</TITLE>
<META NAME="author" CONTENT="Mikey">
<META NAME="date" CONTENT="08/20/2013">
</HEAD>
<BODY style="margin-top:0;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt; color:#000000">
<DIV style="width:624px"><P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>AMENDED AND RESTATED</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>OF</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>TECTON CORPORATION</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>A Nevada Corporation</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify><B>THE UNDERSIGNED</B>, under the provisions of and subject to the requirements of the laws of the State of Nevada, do make, record and file these Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation, in writing, and do hereby certify:</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE I.</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>NAME</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The name of the corporation shall be Tecton Corporation and shall be governed by Chapter 78 of the Nevada Revised Statutes.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE II.</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>NATURE AND PURPOSE</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The nature of the business shall be to engage in any and all lawful activity permitted by the laws of the State of Nevada and desirable to support the continued existence of the corporation.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The corporation shall have the power to conduct its business both within and without the State of Nevada. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE III.</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>PRINCIPAL OFFICE</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The principal office of the corporation shall be: 15500 Roosevelt Blvd., Suite 303, Clearwater, FL &nbsp;33760.</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE IV.</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>CAPITAL STOCK</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The total authorized capital stock of the corporation shall be One Hundred Ten Million (110,000,000) shares. </P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>One Hundred Million (100,000,000) shares &nbsp;shall be common stock with a par value of $.01 per share, all or any part of which capital stock may be paid for in cash, in property or in labor and services at a fair valuation to be fixed by the Board of Directors. &nbsp;Such stock may be issued from time to time without any action by the stockholders for such consideration as may be fixed from time to time by the Board of Directors, and shares so issued, the full consideration for which has been paid or delivered shall be deemed the fully paid up stock, and the holder of </P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR>
<BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:11pt" align=center>Page <FONT style="font-size:12pt"><B>1</B></FONT> of <B>3</B></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt; page-break-before:always" align=justify>such shares shall not be liable for any further payment thereof. &nbsp;Each share of stock shall have voting privileges and will be eligible for dividends.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>Ten Million (10,000,000) shares &nbsp;shall be preferred stock, par value of $.001 per share, whose voting powers, designations, preferences, interest rate, limitations, restrictions and relative rights shall be determined from time to time by resolution of the Board of Directors of the corporation.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE V.</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>GOVERNING BOARD</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The governing board of this corporation shall be known as Directors, which shall consist of not less than one (1) Director and not more than fifteen (15) Directors and the number of the Directors may from time to time be increased or decreased in such manner provided by the By-Laws of this corporation, provided that the number of Directors shall not be reduced to less than one (1) Director.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The election of the Directors shall be on an annual basis. &nbsp;Each Director shall be of full and legal age. &nbsp;</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>A quorum for the transaction of business shall be a simple majority of the Directors so qualified and present at a meeting. &nbsp;Meetings of the Board of Directors may be held within or without the State of Nevada and members of the Board of Directors need not be stockholders. &nbsp;Attendance at any meeting of the Board of Directors may be in person or by any electronic or telephonic means accessible.</P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=justify><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE VI.</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>INDEMNFICATION</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The corporation shall have the power to indemnify any officer, director or former officer or director to the fullest extent permitted by law.</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE VII.</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>CONSENT TO ACT WITHOUT MEETING</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>If all of the directors severally and collectively consent in writing to any action taken or to be taken by the corporation and the writings evidencing their consent are filed with the Secretary of the Corporation, the action shall be as valid as though it had been authorized at a meeting of the Board of Directors.</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><BR>
<BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:11pt" align=center>Page <FONT style="font-size:12pt"><B>2</B></FONT> of <B>3</B></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt; page-break-before:always" align=center>ARTICLE IX</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>ACQUISITION OF CONTROLLING INTEREST</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The Corporation elects not to be governed by the terms and provisions of Sections 78.378 through 78.3793, inclusive, of the Nevada Revised Statutes, as the same may be amended, superseded, or replaced by any successor section, statute, or provision. </P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center>ARTICLE X</P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=center><B>COMBINATIONS WITH INTERESTED STOCKHOLDERS</B></P>
<P style="margin:0px" align=center><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify>The Corporation elects not to be governed by the terms and provisions of Sections 78.411 through 78.444, inclusive, of the Nevada Revised Statutes, as the same may be amended, superseded, or replaced by any successor section, statute, or provision.</P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:6.667px"><BR></P>
<H1 style="margin-top:0px">Endnotes</H1>
<P style="margin-top:6.667px; margin-bottom:6.667px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify><I>The undersigned, in pursuance of general corporation laws of the State of Nevada, does make and file this Certificate, hereby declaring and certifying the facts herein above stated are true and correct, and accordingly has set his hand this 22nd day of July, 2013.</I></P>
<P style="margin:6.667px"><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-top:0px; font-size:10pt" cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><TR height=0 style="font-size:0"><TD width=295.2 /></TR>

</TABLE>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><I>MICAH ELDRED</I></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><I>President and Chairman of the Board</I></P>
<P style="margin:6.667px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" align=justify><I>I, Christine Zitman, being the duly elected and presently serving Secretary of the above named corporation hereby certify that the vote by which the stockholders holding shares in the corporation entitling them to exercise a least a majority of the voting power have voted in favor of the amendments is: 1,452,412 or 58.4% of issued and outstanding shares.</I></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<TABLE style="margin-top:0px; font-size:10pt" cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><TR height=0 style="font-size:0"><TD width=295.2 /></TR>

<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><I>Christine Zitman</I></P>
<P style="margin:0px; font-family:Calibri,Times New Roman; font-size:12pt"><I>Secretary</I></P>
<P style="margin:0px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px"><BR></P>
<P style="margin:6.667px"><BR>

<P style="margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:12.2px"><BR></P>
